title.narrative: ACCESS/QUALITY EDUCATION

description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and youth have increased access to inclusive and quality formal and non-formal education., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.

title.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and youth have increased access to inclusive and quality formal and non-formal education.

description.narrative: UNICEF support resulted in the successful roll-out of the back-to-school campaign, safe school protocols, and enhanced capacity of the education sector to ensure prevention and control measures in schools, benefiting 1.5 million girls and boys. UNICEF also supported children’s access to ;formal education and contributed to the development of quality education. Meanwhile, 10,602 girls and boys (including non-Libyan children) were reached through non-formal education. A roadmap for distance education was developed. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
